The trends it identified are:


Consolidation and partnerships amidst funding slowdown;
Prior authorization efficiency;
Innovating to ease provider burden;
New patient engagement and distribution models;
GenAI and the future of patient engagement; and
CancerX is accelerating cancer treatment innovations.

The 2023 winners each earned a $60,000 cash prize. They are: 


AgingSense - Wearable technology to monitor heart failure symptoms and response to treatment;
Cardiost - An implantable medical device to improve quality of life among heart failure patients;
Gravitrex - A mechanically powered assistive device to help people regain or improve their ability to walk;
Lantern Laboratories - A precision medicine device and platform that uses electroencephalogram biomarkers to guide real-time dosing of pain relievers during surgery and intensive care;
PopCheck Technologies - A device that provides remote patient monitoring to predict surgical complications and improve postoperative care; and
Voice-It - An interactive, conversation-based artificial intelligence technology that uses machine learning to assist with pain management.

Eight finalists were named for the Healthy Aging Sandbox Challenge, designed to find digital health solutions to help older adults live independently. During the program, participants will be matched with members of the MA Digital Health Sandbox Network. The finalists are:


Artifcts (Washington D.C.);
Enabled Health (Burlington, Mass.);
MiiCare (Lewes, Del.);
Moneta Health (Washington, D.C.);
Ompractice (Springfield, Mass.);
Onward (San Leandro, Calif.);
REEV (Boston, Mass.); and
SecureSeniorConnections (Based in Scottsdale, AZ, with workforce in Mass.).

The CEO of 11TEN Innovation Partners, James Lewis, shared his takeaways from ViVE 2023 including:


AI was a hot topic, with numerous companies showcasing potential in healthcare;
Improved access to care and health equity through data and technology was a prominent discussion point;
Cedars Sinai Accelerator's model for healthcare systems working with startups is exemplary. 11TEN plans to learn from it to help bring similar accelerator programs to healthcare system partners across the country; and
Consumer tech was scarce, with most technologies and business models focused on B2B solutions.

The future of aging depends on products and technologies that deliver and motivate older users to jump in again and again, says Rendever. The company recommends some of the most popular experiences that industry leaders should strive to deliver in this space include:


Travel and bucket list experiences;
Community building;
Connecting with family members;
Reminiscense therapy; and
Fitness.
